sentences.english: A footnote is made at the bottom of the page.
Clerk says if I tear pages out of a book I have to buy it.

sentences.english: Even now, the match does not stop changes the page.
sentences.chinese: 即使現在，對手也不停地翻動書頁。

sentences.english: Every day without you like a book without pages.
sentences.chinese: 沒有你的日子就像一本沒有書頁的書，勃然無味。

sentences.english: The book lay open on the table.
sentences.chinese: 這本書的書頁沒有裁開。

sentences.english: The pupil bent the corners of the pages in and damage them.
sentences.chinese: 這名小學生把頁角向內折，弄壞了書頁。

sentences.english: Page curatiue Zhang, paper cutting machine with a single side of a page will be trimmed to the desired size.
sentences.chinese: 頁張理齊後，用單面切紙機把書頁裁切成所需的大小。

sentences.english: When he turned the pages, the top of his head in the branches have something shook up.
sentences.chinese: 當他翻動書頁時，他頭頂的樹枝中有樣東西晃動起來。

sentences.english: The tang of Scotch , sweat and gun-metal rose from his pages.
sentences.chinese: 他的書頁中泛起蘇格蘭的，汗水和炮銅的濃烈氣息。

sentences.english: The most pages of this book are all dog-eared .

sentences.english: The pages of the dictionary had curled up from constant use.
sentences.chinese: 字典的書頁由於經常使用都捲起來了。

sentences.english: It ruins a book to double back the pages as a bookmark.
sentences.chinese: 把書頁折起來當作書籤用會把書弄壞的。

sentences.english: Aziraphale turned a few of the yellowed pages.
sentences.chinese: 亞茨拉菲爾翻了翻泛黃的書頁。

sentences.english: Pagination the numbering of the make-up pages in consecutive order of a book.
sentences.chinese: 在拼版後的書頁加上順序頁碼的情況。

sentences.english: The shelves are loaded with old musty books whose pages have become yellowish.
sentences.chinese: 書架上堆着發黴的舊書，書頁已經又黃又脆。
